{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s001", "order": 1, "text": "**Feasibility Study: Secure Sharing with Verifiable Logs**", "char_start": 0, "char_end": 58, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 10}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s002", "order": 2, "text": "---", "char_start": 60, "char_end": 63, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 1}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s003", "order": 3, "text": "### **Objective – Secure Sharing with Verifiable Logs**", "char_start": 65, "char_end": 120, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 10}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s004", "order": 4, "text": "This feasibility study explores the development and deployment of a secure data-sharing system with verifiable audit logs, tailored to highly regulated environments.", "char_start": 122, "char_end": 287, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 26}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s005", "order": 5, "text": "The primary objective is to enable entities (e.g., enterprises, healthcare providers, government agencies) to share sensitive data across organizational boundaries without compromising confidentiality, integrity, or regulatory compliance.", "char_start": 288, "char_end": 526, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 35}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s006", "order": 6, "text": "The solution ensures that:", "char_start": 527, "char_end": 553, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 5}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s007", "order": 7, "text": "- Data is encrypted before leaving the client’s environment.", "char_start": 555, "char_end": 615, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 11}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s008", "order": 8, "text": "- Access and sharing actions are logged in a tamper-proof manner.", "char_start": 616, "char_end": 681, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 14}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s009", "order": 9, "text": "- Regulatory frameworks such as GDPR are upheld.", "char_start": 682, "char_end": 730, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 9}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s010", "order": 10, "text": "- Stakeholders retain cryptographic proof of compliance activities.", "char_start": 731, "char_end": 798, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 9}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s011", "order": 11, "text": "---", "char_start": 800, "char_end": 803, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 1}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s012", "order": 12, "text": "### **Encryption Model – Client-Side AES-GCM with Key Escrow via KMS-Backed HSM**", "char_start": 805, "char_end": 886, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 20}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s013", "order": 13, "text": "To ensure end-to-end confidentiality, all data is encrypted on the client side using **AES-GCM (Advanced Encryption Standard in Galois/Counter Mode)** before transmission or storage.", "char_start": 888, "char_end": 1070, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 38}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s014", "order": 14, "text": "This authenticated encryption algorithm ensures both data confidentiality and integrity, guarding against unauthorized access and tampering.", "char_start": 1071, "char_end": 1211, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 18}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s015", "order": 15, "text": "Key characteristics of the encryption model include:", "char_start": 1213, "char_end": 1265, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 8}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s016", "order": 16, "text": "- **Client-side encryption**:", "char_start": 1267, "char_end": 1296, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 8}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s017", "order": 17, "text": "Data is encrypted before it leaves the user’s device or service boundary.", "char_start": 1297, "char_end": 1370, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 14}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s018", "order": 18, "text": "- **AES-GCM**:", "char_start": 1371, "char_end": 1385, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 7}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s019", "order": 19, "text": "Offers authenticated encryption with additional data (AEAD), ensuring integrity in transit and at rest.", "char_start": 1386, "char_end": 1489, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 18}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s020", "order": 20, "text": "- **Key Management**: Keys are not stored with the data.", "char_start": 1490, "char_end": 1546, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 14}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s021", "order": 21, "text": "Instead, they are escrowed via a **cloud-based Key Management Service (KMS)** integrated with **Hardware Security Modules (HSMs)** for secure generation, rotation, and access control.", "char_start": 1547, "char_end": 1730, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 38}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s022", "order": 22, "text": "- **Access Control Policies**: Access to the keys is governed by strict Identity and Access Management (IAM) roles and time-based constraints.", "char_start": 1731, "char_end": 1873, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 29}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s023", "order": 23, "text": "- **Auditability**:", "char_start": 1874, "char_end": 1893, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 5}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s024", "order": 24, "text": "Every key retrieval attempt is logged and monitored within the KMS system.", "char_start": 1894, "char_end": 1968, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 13}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s025", "order": 25, "text": "This model effectively mitigates the risks of insider threats, data breaches, and unauthorized key access.", "char_start": 1970, "char_end": 2076, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 18}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s026", "order": 26, "text": "---", "char_start": 2078, "char_end": 2081, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 1}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s027", "order": 27, "text": "### **Blockchain Logging – Append-Only Hash to Hyperledger; On-Chain Proof Every 10 Minutes**", "char_start": 2083, "char_end": 2176, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 20}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s028", "order": 28, "text": "For verifiable, tamper-evident logging of data-sharing events, an **append-only audit trail** is constructed using a **Hyperledger Fabric** blockchain network.", "char_start": 2178, "char_end": 2337, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 33}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s029", "order": 29, "text": "This system logs cryptographic hashes of metadata related to each data-sharing operation.", "char_start": 2338, "char_end": 2427, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 15}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s030", "order": 30, "text": "**Mechanics of the logging model:**", "char_start": 2429, "char_end": 2464, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 7}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s031", "order": 31, "text": "- **Off-chain event processing**:", "char_start": 2466, "char_end": 2499, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 9}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s032", "order": 32, "text": "Every data-sharing event (including metadata like sender, recipient, and timestamp) is hashed (e.g., SHA-256) and temporarily stored in an event buffer.", "char_start": 2500, "char_end": 2652, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 33}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s033", "order": 33, "text": "- **Hash chaining**:", "char_start": 2653, "char_end": 2673, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 6}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s034", "order": 34, "text": "Events are grouped and sequentially hashed to form a Merkle tree.", "char_start": 2674, "char_end": 2739, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 12}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s035", "order": 35, "text": "- **On-chain commitment**:", "char_start": 2740, "char_end": 2766, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 8}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s036", "order": 36, "text": "Every **10 minutes**, a Merkle root representing the last batch of events is written to the blockchain.", "char_start": 2767, "char_end": 2870, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 21}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s037", "order": 37, "text": "- **Hyperledger Fabric**: Chosen for its enterprise readiness, fine-grained access controls, and support for private channels between consortium members.", "char_start": 2871, "char_end": 3024, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 27}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s038", "order": 38, "text": "- **Auditability**:", "char_start": 3025, "char_end": 3044, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 5}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s039", "order": 39, "text": "Any external auditor or regulatory authority can verify an event’s inclusion by validating the Merkle proof against the on-chain hash.", "char_start": 3045, "char_end": 3179, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 24}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s040", "order": 40, "text": "This ensures non-repudiation, tamper evidence, and cryptographic traceability for all shared events.", "char_start": 3181, "char_end": 3281, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 15}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s041", "order": 41, "text": "---", "char_start": 3283, "char_end": 3286, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 1}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s042", "order": 42, "text": "### **GDPR Alignment – Right-to-Erasure via Off-Chain Pointer Deletion; Article 30 Mapping**", "char_start": 3288, "char_end": 3380, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 21}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s043", "order": 43, "text": "The solution is engineered to comply with the **General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)**, focusing on data subject rights and controller obligations.", "char_start": 3382, "char_end": 3534, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 27}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s044", "order": 44, "text": "**Key Compliance Mechanisms:**", "char_start": 3536, "char_end": 3566, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 5}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s045", "order": 45, "text": "- **Right-to-Erasure**:", "char_start": 3568, "char_end": 3591, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 9}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s046", "order": 46, "text": "Although the system maintains immutable logs on-chain, actual data is never stored on the blockchain.", "char_start": 3592, "char_end": 3693, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 19}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s047", "order": 47, "text": "Instead:\n  - All personally identifiable information (PII) resides off-chain in encrypted form.", "char_start": 3694, "char_end": 3789, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 18}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s048", "order": 48, "text": "- On-chain entries merely reference **pseudonymous pointers** or **non-PII metadata**.\n  - When a right-to-erasure request is granted, the corresponding off-chain data and its reference pointer are deleted.", "char_start": 3792, "char_end": 3998, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 41}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s049", "order": 49, "text": "This ensures data is no longer accessible or re-identifiable, satisfying Article 17 obligations.", "char_start": 3999, "char_end": 4095, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 15}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s050", "order": 50, "text": "- **Article 30 Mapping (Records of Processing Activities)**:\n  -", "char_start": 4097, "char_end": 4161, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 14}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s051", "order": 51, "text": "The system automatically logs data processing activities (who shared what, when, and with whom).\n  -", "char_start": 4162, "char_end": 4262, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 20}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s052", "order": 52, "text": "These logs can be exported in a structured format to facilitate compliance audits.", "char_start": 4263, "char_end": 4345, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 14}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s053", "order": 53, "text": "- **Data Minimization and Purpose Limitation**:\n  - Only metadata essential for compliance is retained.", "char_start": 4347, "char_end": 4450, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 18}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s054", "order": 54, "text": "- Data sharing is purpose-bound and access-controlled.", "char_start": 4453, "char_end": 4507, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 12}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s055", "order": 55, "text": "This hybrid on/off-chain architecture supports both GDPR-compliant data deletion and audit integrity.", "char_start": 4509, "char_end": 4610, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 19}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s056", "order": 56, "text": "---", "char_start": 4612, "char_end": 4615, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 1}
{"doc_id": "40f92fb0-9cee-59ed-8660-b0def183f696", "req_id": "REQ-136", "sent_id": "REQ-136::s057", "order": 57, "text": "### **Cost-Benefit Analysis – Infra Cost vs Compliance Gains**", "char_start": 4617, "char_end": 4679, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 13}
